fields.body:
"But I must explain to you how all this mistaken idea of denouncing pleasure and praising pain was born and I will give you a complete account of the system, and expound the actual teachings of the great explorer of the truth, the master-builder of human happiness. No one rejects, dislikes, or avoids pleasure itself, because it is pleasure, but because those who do not know how to pursue pleasure rationally encounter consequences that are extremely painful.

Nor again is there anyone who loves or pursues or desires to obtain pain of itself, because it is pain, but because occasionally circumstances occur in which toil and pain can procure him some great pleasure. To take a trivial example, which of us ever undertakes laborious physical exercise, except to obtain some advantage from it? But who has any right to find fault with a man who chooses to enjoy a pleasure that has no annoying consequences, or one who avoids a pain that produces no resultant pleasure?"

fields.introduction: Explore data on over 50 LGBT and Sex Work Organisations across Uganda

fields.summary: We work towards a Uganda of total justice devoid of discrimination based on sexual orientation and free of HIV/AIDS and its disastrous effects.

BRU was established to empower the LGBT and sex worker community in Kasese socially, politically and economically through advocacy, economic empowerment, creating awareness, building self-esteem, education and provision of moral support.
COPTEC is a safe space for transgender, transsexual and transvestite people who are infected with HIV, engage in sex work and live in Uganda.
Freedom and Roam Uganda (FARUG) is a Lesbian, Bisexual and Queer (LBQ) diverse persons and womxn’s rights organisation based in Uganda and established in 2003.

We are a youth led human rights organization working with the minority sections of the community especially those marginalized and living under stigma like HIV/AIDS. This also includes the entire LGBTI community (men who have sex with men a
fields.about: We are a youth led human rights organization working with the minority sections of the community especially those marginalized and living under stigma like HIV/AIDS. This also includes the entire LGBTI community (men who have sex with men and transgender persons, sex workers (SW), Refugees and victims of Drug Abuse.

fields.summary: iFreedom Uganda provides a free and secure Internet Environment where the marginalized members of the Ugandan LGBTI and sex workers communities can freely express themselves without any fear of risk and reprisal from state agencies and oth
fields.about: iFreedom Uganda provides a free and secure Internet Environment where the marginalized members of the Ugandan LGBTI and sex workers communities can freely express themselves without any fear of risk and reprisal from state agencies and other dangerous hacking groups.

fields.summary: MAHIPSO was formed with a primary motive of promoting access to friendly healthcare, justice, and legal aid services for structurally excluded women

TYI is a rural youth led human rights organisation that exists to uphold, advocate and advance the health and human rights of rural transgender and gender diverse youth communities in Uganda but specifically western Uganda.
fields.about: TYI is a rural transgender youth women, transgender youth sex workers and gender diverse youth led human rights organization that exists to uphold, advocate and advance the health and human rights of rural transgender and gender diverse youth communities in Uganda but specifically western Uganda.

fields.summary: ERWEO aims to empower and improve the well-being of LBT women and female sex workers through community mobilisation.
Visual Echoes was founded to advocate for the rights and freedoms of sexual minority groups in Uganda through sports, Visual Art and Culture as well as providing legal aid services.
fields.about: Visual Echoes is a registered youth Lesbians, Gay men, Bisexuals, Transgender, and sex workers-led organisation founded in 2017 to advocate for the rights and freedoms of sexual minority groups in Uganda through sports, Visual Art and Culture as well as providing legal aid services to LGBTIQ people.

fields.summary: At Key Populations Uganda, we serve a wide-ranging group of minority groups and marginalized communities within Uganda who are particularly vulnerable to HIV and lack adequate access to services.
HOPE Mbale is a non-profit organisation that promotes and advocates for human rights observance, quality health service provision and equal opportunities for all.
TNU was established with the aim of supporting coordination and collaboration among trans and gender diverse persons’ organisations.
Our mission is provide health services to the MSM community in Uganda and advocate for the recognition, protection, and actualization of their rights
Let’s Walk Uganda strives to provide LGBT+ individuals in Uganda with needs-based protection and response services so that they can live dignified and independent lives.
UNESO is an umbrella body for organizations led by sex workers for sex workers.
SWING is working for the promotion of human rights and health for male and trans sex workers
MONU is a sex-worker-led organisation dedicated to supporting and advocating for human rights and social justice for male sex workers within Uganda
WOPEIN is a sex -worker-led organisation that advocates for and promotes demand, access and utilisation of health services for sex workers in Uganda

Fem Alliance is a LBTQ organization which was established by a group of lesbians who felt that the needs of the growing LBTQ community was not adequately represented by the few minority groups organizations in Uganda.
WWM promotes gender equality & human rights of women, minorities and other vulnerable groups.
SLUM is a sex-worker-led civil society organisation established by and for young women sex workers in slums of greater Kampala

EADWA is committed to serve the general population of female sex workers that are striving to access health services by advocating for an enabling environment, favorable laws and policies, and increased access to health services
A feminist group that exists to address social, economic oppressions imposed on women refugees and native sex work because of gender, class, race, sexual orientation

JEEWAG was established to campaign, advocate, fight and challenge issues affecting sex workers’ lives, feminists in fish landing sites particularly those experiencing multiple social, health, legal and economic disadvantages in Uganda.
WERAIN brings attention to the human rights of marginalized individuals and groups in the West Nile region through advocacy, leadership, and development skills.
TRIUMPH is an indigenous organization that advocates for the inclusion and rights of persons with psycho-social disabilities.

AWAC was established to build a resilient female sex workers’ movement that advocate for sustainable integrated health, promotion of human rights, social and economic well-being of female sex workers.
